<dl id="n11119d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11119d">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11119d"> 119(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> visage accompagn&eacute; de</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Lucile]</font> Lucile &eacute;tait grande et d&apos;une beaut&eacute; remarquable, mais s&eacute;rieuse. Son <mark>visage p&acirc;le &eacute;tait accompagn&eacute; de</mark> longs cheveux noirs; elle attachait souvent au ciel ou promenait autour d&apos;elle des regards pleins de tristesse ou de feu. <br><font color="green">[Lucile was tall and endowed with a remarkable, but solemn beauty. Her pale face was framed in her long black hair; she often gazed heavenwards or glanced about her with looks full of sadness or fire.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i>M&eacute;moires d&apos;outre-tombe</i> 32</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
